Rating: 4
This is a fantastic dish. Amazingly flavorful, vegan, and even fairly suitable for a rawtarian. I often double it and have days worth. I find quinoa cooked in vegetable broth to offer a better texture and nutritive value than bulgur, which also, I believe, makes it gluten-free. I make this often enough that I just add more rice and/or cider vinegar along with leftover tarragon to a bottle so it's ready for the next batch. Up the walnuts, add a drizzle of walnut oil...

