Rating: 3
Easy to make and a great vegetarian dish. I added lemon juice with dijon mustard to give it a bit of zing and added some cubed avocado for some creamy texture. Both went great with the nuts, lentils and chewy bulgur wheat.

Rating: 4
I've made this recipe a few times already. I use the precooked lentils from TJ's, and bulgar cooked in broth to start with. First time, I made it with red pepper, sun-dried tomatoes, kalamata olives, and walnuts with tarragon and parsley, then garnished with good feta. We gobbled it up. it paired great with grilled trout topped with blistered cherry tomatoes and a parsley, tarragon, lemon vinaigrette and was an impressive meal fit for guests. Second time I stuck a little more to the recipe in terms of vegetables, but had only mint and parsley. I still added sundried tomatoes. I took it to a potluck and got tons of compliments. This will be a staple, and we love that it tastes great but is still very healthy!

Rating: 3
Very easy to make. I didn't have all of the ingredients - had to substitute red wine vinegar for tarragon vinegar (though I added plenty of fresh tarragon) and used red onion instead of shallot. To make this a bit lighter I used only 2 T of oil and I only had 1/4 cup of walnuts - but the results are great! Light & fluffy. I'll definitely make it again.

Rating: 4
This was marvelous. However, I doctored mine up with some additional items which made a huge difference in the overall taste. First, I added sun-dried tomatoes and feta cheese per a previous poster's recommendation. I also doubled my recipe, however, I went easy on the tarragon (I only used what the original recipe called for). I did not have tarragon vinegar so I used white wine vinegar and was very generous with it. (I probably used more like 1/4 cup for the whole salad). Lastly, I added Greek Kalamata olives spread into the mix (diced olives will do). This made a huge difference and really put the finishing touches on the salad. My only complaint is the amount of time that it took to pull it all together. After chopping the ingredients and waiting for the lentils and bulgar to cool, about 3 hours had passed before I was finished. Nonetheless it was great and I will definitely make this again!

